The 2D test case for probing rotation-treatment numerical models. The original experimental data were 
ontained using PIV in a in a 6° diverging rotating channel. The camera was stiffly connected to the
rotating channel and allowed to measure relative velocities.


More information about experiments:

1. Alberto Di Sante, René Van den Braembussche
"Experimental and Numerical Investigation of the Flow in a Rotating Diverging Channel"
2. Alberto Di Sante, Javier Gonzalez Castaño, René A. Van den Braembussche
"Time Resolved PIV in a Rotating Diverging Channel"




